  "texts": [
    "Formative assessments, which aim to improve writing proficiency through ongoing interaction, necessitate providing feedback to essay authors (Havnes et al. 2012; Owen 2016).",
    "Hence, building a deep learning-based AES that not only assesses essays but also generate insightful feedback holds immense value for formative writing assessments.",
    "There are few studies that address the issue of feedback generation in AES models by incorporating traits (Hussein et al. 2020), providing explianability (Kumar and Boulanger 2020), and identifying useful sentences from essays to be used as feedback (Dong et al. 2017; Woods et al. 2017; Fiacco et al. 2022 Fiacco et al., 2023)).",
    "In this survey paper, we start by examining related surveys on deep learning-based AES.",
    "We have compiled a summary of several survey papers on deep learning-based AES published in the last five years, which is presented in Table 1.The table outlines the main themes of each survey paper, along with topics relevant to AES research such as model types, feedback generation, and dataset."
